The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                                           6                                                                                      Business Briefs
                              
	 Mumbai, June 29: Inflation is likely to come down to 5 per cent by the end of the fiscal from the present double digit level mainly on base effect and also with the fall in deficit, chief economic adviser Kaushik Basu said here today. I think the forecast of 5 per cent inflation by March 2011 is a reasonable forecast... the large figure of inflation in the last couple of months was because of the higher base effect, Basu said.                            
	 New Delhi, June 29: The Telecom Regulatory Authority of India (Trai) will switch to a quarterly audit of the Quality of Service. At present, the service providers submit data on the defined parameters of the Quality of Service every three months, but audit is done annually by Trai.                             
	 New Delhi, June 29: The government has shortlisted ICICI Securities, SBI Capital, Merrill Lynch-SMC, UBS and Kotak Mahindra Capital to manage the Rs 4,000-crore public issue of Hindustan Copper.                             
	 Mumbai, June 29: Drug firm Alembic will hive-off its pharmaceutical business and merge it with its wholly owned group firm  Alembic Pharma Ltd.                             
	 New Delhi, June 29: Indias sugar production is expected to touch 23 million tonnes in the next crop year starting October on the back of higher area falling under cane production.
                                                                                                                          
